								<h1>How it works</h1>
								<p>
									We are checking your CI builds for messages and display the corresponding badge, based on your settings.
								</p>
								<p>
									Replace the image of your badge with a link to our API. The link contains all the information we need to generate the badge. Example:
									<pre class="code">
&lt;img src="https://nabble.io/api/v1/appveyor/Dresel/SampleProject/StyleCop" /&gt;
</pre>
								</p>
							</div>
							<div class="edit-tab tab-pane" id="prereq">
								<div class="teb-icon-edit">
									<i class="fa fa-cogs"></i>
								</div>
								<h1>Prerequisites</h1>
								<p>
									In order to access the analyzer results of your CI build,
									we need the results of your analyzer as build artefacts.
									The report has to be called <strong>report.json</strong>.
									In case there are more than one report.json, the results will be summed up.
									The format of the log follows the <a href="https://github.com/sarif-standard/sarif-spec">SARIF standard</a>.<br />
									More info can be found in the <a href="https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn/blob/master/docs/compilers/Error%20Log%20Format.md">roslyn repository</a>.<br />
								</p>
								<p>
									For an example how to set it up, have a look at our
									<a href="https://github.com/SpatialFocus/SampleProject/blob/analyzer-integration/SampleProject/SampleProject.csproj#L29">Spatial Focus SampleProject</a>.
								</p>
								<p>
									For an example how to configure the build artifacts, have a look at our
									<a href="https://github.com/SpatialFocus/SampleProject/blob/analyzer-integration/appveyor.yml#L9">AppVeyor.yml file</a>,
									which triggers AppVeyor to store the report as a build artifact.
									This allows our REST interface to access the report and analyze it.
								</p>
							</div>
